    <h1>Knowing How</h1>
    <blockquote>
      <p>“I’ve long argued that UI design, programming, and product strategy should be learned apprentice-style with your hands and through experience, not through school and pedagogy. When I go to conferences about design I see a lot of declarative knowledge. Knowledge of. The latest CSS rules. The new JavaScript syntax. Ten ways to make users happy (supposedly) or whatever else.</p>

      <p>What I don’t see are procedures—somebody standing up there with a pen or a text editor and making things happen and showing how it’s done. That’s what I want to see and that’s what I think our industry needs more of.”</p>

