    <h1>Cheatsheet for your app</h1>
    <ul>
      <li>
        Your Ruby on Rails app can be found at:<br />
        <code>projects/railsgirls</code>
      <li>
      <li>
        You can start your app by opening Terminal and:<br />
        <code>cd projects/railsgirls rails s</code>
      </li>
      <li>
        Access the app:<br />
        Open <code>http://localhost:3000</code> on your web browser
      </li>
      <li>
        Most of the time you edit the files at <code>app/</code> directory<br />
        <code>app/views/</code> (the user interfaces of your app)<br />
        <code>app/models/</code> (models define app information structure)<br />
        <code>app/controllers/</code> (are the glue between models and views)
      </li>
      <li>
        Tools we use

        <ul>
          <li>Bootstrap (to style the app)</li>
          <li>Sublime/Komodo/Vim (to edit the code files) <a href="http://goo.gl/IKh1">http://goo.gl/IKh1</a></li>
          <li>Heroku (to host the application) <a href="http://heroku.com">http://heroku.com</a></li>
        </ul>
      </li>
    </ul>
